ists  Jean Plaidy  (  Eleanor Hibbert ,  1910–93 ) and  Jean Rhys  (  Ella Gwendolen Rees Williams ,  1894–1979 ), British actress  Jean Simmons  (  1929–2010 ), and American-born actress  Jean Seberg  (  1938–79 ). It is also found as a variant spelling of the masculine name   Gene ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."]},{"name":"Jeane","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jean ."]}]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["1  ♂ ‘Profit’ or ‘sharp’.","2  ♀, ♂ ‘Upright’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jean II de Haveskerque was born in 1270, in Haverskerque, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France, his father, Jean le Fosseux de Haverkerque, was 30 and his mother, Ermenthude d'Aire, was 28. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Beatrix d'Aisne of Essex. He died in 1302, in France, at the age of 32."},"et":{"1270–1302":"1270–1302","1260–1302":"1260–1302","1271–Female":"1271–Surnud","1305–1347":"1305–1347","–Female":"Surnud","1240–1284":"1240–1284","1242–1291":"1242–1291","1305":"1305","1347":"1347","1302":"1302","1242":"1242","1284":"1284","before 1260":"enne 1260","1240":"1240","1271":"1271","1260":"1260","1270":"1270","1291":"1291","Haverskerque, Nord, Hauts-de-France, France":"Haverskerque, Nord, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Haverskerque, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Haverskerque, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1270–1302":"1270–1302","1260–1302":"1260–1302","1271–Female":"1271–Kuollut","1305–1347":"1305–1347","–Female":"Kuollut","1240–1284":"1240–1284","1242–1291":"1242–1291","1305":"1305","1347":"1347","1302":"1302","1242":"1242","1284":"1284","before 1260":"ennen vuotta 1260","1240":"1